 Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Beatrix de Villiers was born in 1368, in Brooksby, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of John Sir de Villiers. She had at least 3 daughters with John Bagot. She died in 1429, in Blithfield, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1368–1429":"1368–1429","1354–Male":"1354–Surnud","1358–1436":"1358–1436","1430–1480":"1430–1480","1380–1450":"1380–1450","1395–1452":"1395–1452","1410–1509":"1410–1509","1327–1416":"1327–1416","25 Nov 1416":"25. november 1416","1395":"1395","1450":"1450","1480":"1480","1380":"1380","1327":"1327","1436":"1436","1358":"1358","1368":"1368","1410":"1410","1354":"1354","1452":"1452","1430":"1430","1509":"1509","Abt 1380":"umbes 1380","1429":"1429","1416":"1416","Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, , England":"Melton Mowbray, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Brooksby, Leicestershire, , England":"Brooksby, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Blithfield, Staffordshire, , England":"Blithfield, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Blithfield, Staffordshire, England":"Blithfield, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1368–1429":"1368–1429","1354–Male":"1354–Kuollut","1358–1436":"1358–1436","1430–1480":"14